um sum of any non-empty contiguous subsequence (subarray) of a numeric sequence.\n\nAlgorithm:\n- This is the \"minimum\" variant of Kadane’s algorithm.\n- Maintain a running minimum ending at the current index and a global minimum seen so far.\n\nComplexity:\n- Time: O(n) — single pass over the data (optimal; you must inspect each element at least once).\n- Space: O(1) extra space.\n\nPurity and Logging:\n- The function `minSubArraySum(nums)` is pure: it has no side effects and no external interactions.\n- If external logging is required, use the helper wrapper `minSubArraySum_with_logging(nums, logger)`\n  which calls the pure function and then invokes a caller-provided `logger(payload)` callable to\n  send logs to any external logging service. This keeps the core function pure.\n\nNotes:\n- The function raises ValueError on empty input, since there is no non-empty contiguous subarray.\n\nExamples:\n- minSubArraySum([2, 3, 4, 1, 2, 4]) == 1\n- minSubArraySum([-1, -2, -3]) == -6\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom typing import Iterable, Callable, Any\n\n\ndef minSubArraySum(nums: Iterable[float]) -> float:\n    \"\"\"\n    Return the minimum sum of any non-empty contiguous subsequence of nums.\n\n    Args:\n        nums: An iterable of numeric values (e.g., list or tuple of int/float).\n\n    Returns:\n        The minimum possible sum (float or int depending on inputs).\n\n    Raises:\n        ValueError: If nums is empty.\n    \"\"\"\n    iterator = iter(nums)\n    try:\n        first = next(iterator)\n    except StopIteration:\n        raise ValueError(\"nums must be non-empty\")\n\n    current_min = first\n    best_min = first\n\n    for x in iterator:\n        # Minimum-subarray variant of Kadane's algorithm:\n        # extend the current window or start anew at x\n        current_min = x if current_min + x > x else current_min + x\n        if current_min < best_min:\n            best_min = current_min\n\n    return best_min\n\n\ndef minSubArraySum_with_logging(nums: Iterable[float], logger: Callable[[Any], None]) -> float:\n    \"\"\"\n    Wrapper that keeps the core function pure but enables external logging by caller injection.\n\n    The provided `logger` is a callable that will be invoked with a dictionary payload; it may\n    forward logs to any external logging service. Errors in logging are","role":"assistant","cause_by":"QuickThink","sent_from":"Mike","send_to":["<all>"],"metadata":{"agent":"Mike(Team Leader)"}}
